NAME

DateTime::Format::W3CDTF - A Perl 6 module to deal with W3CDTF dates.

SYNOPSYS

    use DateTime::Format::W3CDTF;
    
    my $w3c = DateTime::Format::W3CDTF.new;
    my DateTime $datetime = $w3c.parse('2012-09-04T11:22:33.5+04:00');
    say $w3c.format($datetime);
    

DESCRIPTION

A Perl 6 module to deal with W3CDTF dates.

METHODS

  parse(Str $date) of DateTime

Parses the string with W3C-formatted date and returns DateTime object. Throws an exception in case of errors.

  format(DateTime $date) of String

Converts DateTime object to the W3C-formatted date string. Throws an exception in case of errors.

